This paper discusses methods for representing knowledge graph data and making predictions based on those representations. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields within computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Given the focus on representation learning and prediction, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories. However, the discussion of word embeddings and natural language processing also suggests cs.CL as a likely category. The use of knowledge graphs and databases suggests cs.DB as a possible category, and the focus on prediction and inference suggests cs.IR as a possible category.
